        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The records relate to both the Radical Philosophy Association and to its journal 
                <emph render="italic">Radical Philosophy Review</emph>, and contain correspondence, minutes, typescripts, conference materials membership and financial materials, and printed ephemera and other internal documents related to its political activism, including within the American Philosophical Association.</p>
            <p>FOR ADDITIONAL INFORMATION, CONTACT: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Founded in 1982, the Radical Philosophy Association is an international organization whose members struggle against capitalism, racism, sexism, homophobia, disability discrimination, environmental ruin, and all other forms of domination, drawing upon a variety of radical traditions including phenomenology, Marxism, anarchism, post-structuralism, post-colonial theory and environmentalism. Its efforts center on conferences and publications. The RPA also publishes the journal 
                <emph render="italic">Radical Philosophy Review</emph>.</p>
        </bioghist>
